title:
HANNAH KATSMAN DECEMBER 22, 2009
How to Make Patties from Anything and Everything
directions: All ingredients are optional except for the eggs and flour, along with either fish, meat or vegetables.
ingredients: Start with a dry food processor.
(Add fresh parsley, dill or coriander and chop until fine.)
(Peel and cut an onion in half.
(Add fresh or cooked zucchini, mushrooms, cooked beans, rice, hard cheese or other soft foods.)
(Add raw or cooked meat or fish, including tuna.)
Add flour, oats, breadcrumbs, cracked wheat, or cornmeal.
Form into patties and fry or bake.
